Notebook[{
Cell["\<\
Beyond Gerver: Numerical Explorations of the Moving-Sofa Problem\
\>", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"47718ccc-c4f7-4225-ab0f-873f0da67824"],

Cell["\<\
Asymmetric corridors, S-bends, disk tubes, multi-bend scaling, and the convex \
restriction\
\>", "Subtitle",ExpressionUUID->"d8d73c1f-bc88-422b-8803-e8b9420ef5c5"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Marco Thiel, May 2026 \[LongDash] ",
 ButtonBox["github.com/mthiel74/SofaProblem",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://github.com/mthiel74/SofaProblem"], None}]
}], "Text",
 TextAlignment->Center,
 FontSlant->Italic,ExpressionUUID->"ca6004af-202d-4230-a57c-e45248b03e23"],

Cell["Abstract", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"3702ff9e-584c-4fa3-b928-9e5ef613af75"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A companion to the earlier post reproducing Gerver's 2D bound. Here we run \
the same intersection-of-corridor-poses optimiser through five new geometries \
and record what comes out:\n\n",
 StyleBox["(1)",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " an asymmetric L with arm widths 1 and w \[LessEqual] 1; the optimum A(w) \
traces a near-linear curve.\n",
 StyleBox["(2)",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " a 3D L-tube with a disk cross-section; the best prismatic sofa has volume ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["1.173", TraditionalForm]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Times",ExpressionUUID->
  "57717024-ae86-47a9-9dc4-f82bbc6ef7af"],
 " and the slice-by-slice upper bound is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["1.808", TraditionalForm]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Times",ExpressionUUID->
  "8eb1d4ab-3e59-4a31-8d29-0956d90be181"],
 " (vs. ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["2.220", TraditionalForm]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Times",ExpressionUUID->
  "d746032a-f379-4df0-a295-1eb07b2abea6"],
 " for a square cross-section).\n",
 StyleBox["(3)",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " an S-corridor with two consecutive 90\[Degree] bends; the optimal sofa has \
area ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["1.013", TraditionalForm]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Times",ExpressionUUID->
  "9347d819-4f58-4321-95d9-db8cf792577a"],
 ", and its shape collapses to a near-circular disc.\n",
 StyleBox["(4)",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " an N-bend corridor; we measure how the sofa area S(N) decays with N.\n",
 StyleBox["(5)",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " the convex restriction; the best convex sofa we find has area ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["0.81", TraditionalForm]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Times",ExpressionUUID->
  "12379864-07c7-4d45-8d45-6a5cec4f4b4d"],
 " against the classical analytical target of \[Pi]/2 \[TildeTilde] 1.57."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"1f859e5c-bdb0-46a4-b7e1-857e849ef890"],

Cell["1. Asymmetric L-corridor: area as a function of arm-2 width", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"3dbdb37e-1aff-4282-8ce2-c5de9ed7c356"],

Cell["\<\
Take the classical L-corridor and shrink arm 2 to width w \[LessEqual] 1 \
while leaving arm 1 at width 1. Inner walls still meet at (1, 1). At w = 1 we \
recover Gerver; as w \[Rule] 0 the second arm becomes a slit. Sweep:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b66ccd8a-648d-4d55-9b0c-760f5959d3af"],

