Cell["2. 3D L-tube with disk cross-section", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"d80e3c31-33a0-43b5-9adf-85e53054acb1"],

Cell["\<\
Replace the square cross-section by a disk of unit diameter. At height z \
\[Element] [-1/2, 1/2] the strip width available to that horizontal slice of \
the sofa is w(z) = 2\[Sqrt](1/4 - z\.b2). For a prismatic body of height h \
centred in the disk, the cross-section width is constrained by the narrowest \
slice, w = \[Sqrt](1 - h\.b2), and the volume is V(h) = h \[CenterDot] A(\
\[Sqrt](1 - h\.b2)), using A(w) from Section 1.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"40881d71-feb0-4838-b4bc-f0ef084b91e7"],

