    {
     PaneBox[
      StyleBox["\<\"Figure 3. Prism volume V(h) for the unit-diameter \
disk-tube. The maximum (red dot) sits at h \[TildeTilde] 0.78, w \
\[TildeTilde] 0.63, V \[TildeTilde] 1.17. The dashed line at 1.81 is the \
slice-by-slice upper bound \[Integral] A(w(z))\[ThinSpace]dz, unreachable by \
a rigid body because slices at different z would need different motions. The \
square-tube extrusion at V = 2.22 is shown for comparison.\"\>",
       StripOnInput->False,
       FontFamily->"Helvetica",
       FontSize->10,
       FontSlant->Italic],
      Alignment->Center,
      ImageSize->680]}
   },
   DefaultBaseStyle->"Column",
   GridBoxAlignment->{"Columns" -> {{Center}}},
   GridBoxItemSize->{"Columns" -> {{Automatic}}, "Rows" -> {{Automatic}}},
   GridBoxSpacings->{"Columns" -> {{Automatic}}, "Rows" -> {{0.6}}}],
  "Column"]], "Output",
 CellMargins->{{Inherited, Inherited}, {10, 14}},
 ShowCellLabel->False,
 TextAlignment->Center,ExpressionUUID->"84a1e171-918d-4b44-b576-cca280fbd681"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Take-away: the disk-tube 3D sofa is ",
 StyleBox["strictly smaller",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " than the square-tube one in both achievable and upper-bound senses. The \
square corners help \[LongDash] they let the sofa fill the corridor's \
vertical clearance regardless of horizontal position."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"3fca4445-82ff-4dee-82e1-fbf0f8fccca2"],

Cell["3. The S-corridor: two consecutive 90\[Degree] bends", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"9f2e7d4c-73ed-477b-ab66-a96c8d0c14b7"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Add a second left bend after the first. The corridor is now a stair: ",
 StyleBox["+", "Input"],
 "x \[Rule] +y \[Rule] -x. Total rotation is \[Pi]. Same optimiser, extended \
to \[Theta] \[Element] [0, \[Pi]]:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"e754773b-8372-4fea-aad4-3db7e384d727"],

