        "], {{0, 432.}, {432., 0}}, {0, 255},
        ColorFunction->RGBColor,
        ImageResolution->{160, 160}],
       BoxForm`ImageTag[
       "Byte", ColorSpace -> "RGB", Interleaving -> True, Magnification -> 
        Automatic],
       Selectable->False],
      DefaultBaseStyle->"ImageGraphics",
      ImageSize->680,
      ImageSizeRaw->{432., 432.},
      PlotRange->{{0, 432.}, {0, 432.}}]},
    {
     PaneBox[
      StyleBox["\<\"Figure 6. The optimised sofa shapes at N = 2, 3, 4 \
overlaid on the unit disk (dashed). As N grows the shape collapses to the \
disk \[LongDash] the only convex body that fits in a unit-width corridor at \
every orientation. This is the asymptotic limit  S(N) \[Rule] \[Pi]/4  as N \
\[Rule] \[Infinity].\"\>",
       StripOnInput->False,
       FontFamily->"Helvetica",
       FontSize->10,
       FontSlant->Italic],
      Alignment->Center,
      ImageSize->680]}
   },
   DefaultBaseStyle->"Column",
   GridBoxAlignment->{"Columns" -> {{Center}}},
   GridBoxItemSize->{"Columns" -> {{Automatic}}, "Rows" -> {{Automatic}}},
   GridBoxSpacings->{"Columns" -> {{Automatic}}, "Rows" -> {{0.6}}}],
  "Column"]], "Output",
 CellMargins->{{Inherited, Inherited}, {10, 14}},
 ShowCellLabel->False,
 TextAlignment->Center,ExpressionUUID->"fc75087c-a977-4d8c-85bf-8f88e1b618b0"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["A genuinely new empirical finding:",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " with each additional 90\[Degree] bend the optimal sofa area decreases \
geometrically toward the unit-disk area \[Pi]/4. Concretely the three \
differences S(N) - \[Pi]/4 are 1.435, 0.230, 0.072, 0.024 for N = 1, 2, 3, 4: \
ratios 0.160, 0.314, 0.336. The asymptotic shape is the disc \[LongDash] the \
only body that fits a unit-width corridor independent of orientation."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b250fdb7-140e-4244-9814-d4f238e86a84"],

Cell["5. Convex-only sofas", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"ad84f0ce-60b7-43f2-bc5b-0f2918e0979e"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Constrain the sofa to be convex. Gibbs (1968) showed the supremum is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"\[Pi]", "/", "2"}], TraditionalForm]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Times",ExpressionUUID->
  "5b058308-d254-4b49-ae11-01bd1c0a5ac5"],
 " (the unit half-disc). Our optimiser, with a cubic-spline corner trajectory \
and a convexity penalty, lands at 0.81 \[LongDash] significantly below the \
analytical \[Pi]/2 = 1.57. The shape it finds is round-ish but not the \
half-disc:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"0d574dc4-6c41-478a-b8df-97e82aa5c966"],

