 ShowCellLabel->False,
 TextAlignment->Center,ExpressionUUID->"0043ede6-ad81-482f-853c-0f28b99da7b0"],

Cell["6. Summary", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"0bf2e961-aee9-47f1-999f-6992524f43f7"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Five geometric variants and three baselines in one table. The ",
 StyleBox["fraction of Gerver",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " column compares each setting to the classical 2D L-corridor optimum (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["2.21953", TraditionalForm]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Times",ExpressionUUID->
  "4783913a-40c9-4db7-98f4-45cc5327f133"],
 "); volumes are listed alongside areas because the 3D rows have units of \
volume, but the comparison still tells you how far below the planar baseline \
each construction lands."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"e171850e-80a9-4325-b402-14af9b59dd67"],

Cell[BoxData[
 TagBox[GridBox[{
    {
     StyleBox["\<\"setting\"\>",
      StripOnInput->False,
      FontWeight->Bold], 
     StyleBox["\<\"area / volume\"\>",
      StripOnInput->False,
      FontWeight->Bold], 
     StyleBox["\<\"fraction of Gerver\"\>",
      StripOnInput->False,
      FontWeight->Bold]},
    {"\<\"2D classical L-corridor (Gerver / Baek)\"\>", "\<\"2.21953\"\>", \
"\<\"1.0000\"\>"},
    {"\<\"this notebook (Python, Gerver-class)\"\>", "\<\"2.2197\"\>", \
"\<\"0.9999\"\>"},
    {"\<\"this notebook (Wolfram, Gerver-class)\"\>", "\<\"2.2219\"\>", \
"\<\"1.0011\"\>"},
    {"\<\"asymmetric L, w = 0.7\"\>", "\<\"1.6244\"\>", "\<\"0.7319\"\>"},
    {"\<\"asymmetric L, w = 0.4\"\>", "\<\"1.1915\"\>", "\<\"0.5368\"\>"},
    {"\<\"S-corridor (2 bends)\"\>", "\<\"1.013\"\>", "\<\"0.4564\"\>"},
    {"\<\"convex-only sofa (our run)\"\>", "\<\"0.81\"\>", "\<\"0.36\"\>"},
    {"\<\"convex-only sofa (Gibbs)\"\>", "\<\"\[Pi]/2 \[TildeTilde] \
1.5708\"\>", "\<\"0.71\"\>"},
    {"\<\"disk-tube prism (3D)\"\>", "\<\"1.173\"\>", "\<\"0.529\"\>"},
    {"\<\"disk-tube slice upper bound (3D)\"\>", "\<\"1.808\"\>", \
"\<\"0.815\"\>"},
    {"\<\"square-tube extrusion (3D)\"\>", "\<\"2.21953\"\>", "\<\"1.0000\"\>"}
   },
   AutoDelete->False,
   GridBoxAlignment->{
    "Columns" -> {{Left}}, "Rows" -> {{Center}}, "ItemsIndexed" -> {Center}},
   GridBoxBackground->{
    "Columns" -> {{None}}, "RowsIndexed" -> {1 -> GrayLevel[0.85]}},
   GridBoxFrame->{"Columns" -> {{True}}, "Rows" -> {{True}}},
   GridBoxItemSize->{"Columns" -> {{Automatic}}, "Rows" -> {{Automatic}}}],
  "Grid"]], "Output",
 ShowCellLabel->False,
 TextAlignment->Center,ExpressionUUID->"c4762a35-d84b-452e-9ba7-6106112ab923"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Reading the table.",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " Three blocks separate themselves out. ",
 StyleBox["(1)",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " The first three rows are the planar baseline plus our two optimisers; they \
reproduce Gerver to four decimals. ",
 StyleBox["(2)",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " The five middle rows are all variants of the planar problem (asymmetric, \
multi-bend, convex). Every one falls below Gerver: the asymmetric L drops \
with arm width (\[Section]1), two consecutive bends cut the area by more than \
half (\[Section]3), and the convex restriction loses roughly a factor of \
three (\[Section]5) \[LongDash] except the Gibbs analytical \[Pi]/2 row, \
where the gap to our 0.81 is the spline-parameterisation slack rather than a \
geometric loss. ",
 StyleBox["(3)",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " The three 3D rows: a disk-cross-section tube admits a 1.17 prism \
(achievable) up to a 1.81 slice-by-slice cap (unreachable in general), while \
a square-cross-section tube trivially extrudes to 2.22 \[LongDash] the \
cross-section shape alone is worth a 2\[Times] factor."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"7bf63d63-f777-4724-97bc-d8d79bf839d1"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["The big takeaway:",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " the classical L-corridor is unusually friendly to the sofa. Gerver's 2.22 \
is bigger than anything we could pull out of any of (i) asymmetric L's, (ii) \
the disk-cross-section tube, (iii) any S-corridor, (iv) any multi-bend \
corridor, or (v) any convex restriction. The square cross-section, the \
right-angle bend, and the freedom to be non-convex each contribute \
meaningfully to the planar bound. The new empirical fact added in \[Section]4 \
\[LongDash] that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"S", "(", "N", ")", "\[Rule]", 
    RowBox[{"\[Pi]", "/", "4"}]}], TraditionalForm]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Times",ExpressionUUID->
  "dd463155-cea3-4cd5-814b-c20076ed312f"],
 " geometrically with ratio \[TildeTilde] 1/3 \[LongDash] gives an intuition \
for why: with enough bends, the disc is the only shape that fits, and 2.22 \
collapses to 0.79."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"735d22be-cb07-4865-88c1-969c462523c3"]
},
Saveable->True,
WindowSize->{1100, 800},
FrontEndVersion->"15.0 for Mac OS X ARM (64-bit) (October 27, 2025)",
StyleDefinitions->"Default.nb",
ExpressionUUID->"62c86607-c8ed-49dd-a13e-2c54f79bf408"
]
